{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"heinous-frousy-narwhal","description":"# CHANGELOG.md: git-cliff generate-then-curate from conventional commits\n\n## Why\n\nNo user-facing changelog exists: `docs/release-notes.md` is explicitly the agent-facing contract-change log, and GitHub Releases notes are auto-generated from commits. A survey of nine popular Python tools shows towncrier (pip/pytest) solves a many-contributor merge-conflict problem rebar doesn't have; ruff/uv generate from PR labels via an in-house tool (needs a GitHub PR workflow rebar doesn't have); git-cliff is the only mechanism that converts the conventional-commit discipline rebar already pays for (`feat:`/`fix:`/`build:` subjects) into a changelog for free. Keep-a-Changelog is the convergent shape; rich's CHANGELOG.md is the format exemplar (declared KaC + SemVer, dated sections, compare-link block).\n\n## What\n\n- Add `cliff.toml` with `commit_parsers` mapping: `feat:` → Added; `fix:` → Fixed; breaking (`!` / BREAKING CHANGE) → its own highlighted group; `perf:`/`refactor:` → Changed; `docs:` → Documentation (or drop); drop `build:`/`ci:`/`chore:`/`test:`; `filter_unconventional = false` with a catch-all parser for mixed history (per the documented git-cliff migration pattern for repos with imperfect commit hygiene).\n- Generate `CHANGELOG.md` back through v0.1.0 (accept ledger quality for historical sections), then hand-curate the current cycle's top section. Include `## [Unreleased]` and the compare-link block (rich pattern).\n- Wire into `docs/releasing.md`: the release runbook gains a step — regenerate with git-cliff, then a ~5-minute curation pass of the top section before tagging. Record the dial position: generate-then-edit (pure-generated rejected as ledger-like; mypy-style prose rejected as unsustainable solo — one-line rationale each).\n- Check `[project.urls]` Changelog points at the committed file (a Changelog URL already exists in pyproject — verify target).\n- Verify the release workflow / auto-generated GitHub Releases notes remain unchanged (complementary channel, not replaced).\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: `cliff.toml`, `CHANGELOG.md`, a `docs/releasing.md` step, pyproject urls verification.\nOUT: towncrier/news fragments; changing commit-message conventions; back-editing published GitHub Releases; touching `docs/release-notes.md` (stays agent-facing, cross-link only).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` exists with Keep-a-Changelog headings, an Unreleased section, compare links, and entries back to v0.1.0.\n- [ ] `cliff.toml` maps conventional types per the table above and drops noise types; regeneration is deterministic (running twice produces no diff).\n- [ ] `docs/releasing.md` documents the regenerate + curate step at release time.\n- [ ] Rejected alternatives (towncrier, PR-label generation, GitHub-Releases-only) recorded with one-line rationales on the ticket.","id":"ed57-3657-6d0a-4cca","parent_id":"fc2a-9fa5-def6-4e68","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"CHANGELOG.md: git-cliff generate-then-curate from conventional commits"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783628677317557001,"uuid":"52ecea80-391a-4c3a-a353-75de2f2a84b8"}